snippet.textDisplay: I wrote earlier in the week, that IU has selflessly sacrificed her usual artistry to provide a valuable message the world needs more of. Now having assessed the song and MV a few days later, I MUST take-back of my comment about her sacrificing her artistry. Nothing has been sacrificed in this case, the artistry has merely evolved in more valuable ways than I could have possibly imagined. This joyous song is less about appeasing the art/music critique's sensibility but about providing a voice and shining a light back to the people. IU lives up to her reputation as a people's singer. Her power is in her empathy, love, and ability to listen and pay attention to those around her.  Her love for her friends/family, fans, colleagues, and her own fortitude to seek comfort, healing, and boost self-confidence against her shy nature to be shared with the GP. Just when the world needs a pickup, she came up with this whimsical, joyous, capricious festive celebration of embracing yourself for who you are or want to be. The melodic rhythm and structure are easily digestible and translatable into other music expressions, like classical, folk, for personalization and universality. It is extremely intelligent, selfless, and generous in that respect from a music producer's view. I am really intrigued by how much involvement IU has with all of her videos with how they are storyboarded out. There are so much consistent IU signature visuals and stylings, use of motifs, self-referential symbolism, allegorical and visceral touchpoints throughout her MV even as a series, I can't imagine it all coming from just the director. (Hint: watch the MV for Goblin, check out hairclip, the wallpaper, furniture etc.) Mixing fantasy, viewpoints, trends, social stigma (uncomfortable truth), past references, allusions that are uniquely her without her having to explain everything, but leaving the audience with enough imagination to read between the lines. Celebrity is a song for every day, any festive times, like birthdays, graduations, weddings, anniversaries.  It has legs, it has wings, it sparkles, and it flies. Frankly, it would be great her Celebrity message gets spread in all languages, played in any genre, by other artists or ordinary people as a salutation to humanity and the power of goodness and positivity.

snippet.textDisplay:
not only that, the lyrics also talked abt us in general especially part "indetity on diet", such a beautiful message for us too to love ourselves! this is what IU talked abt this song (song introduction)
"I have a friend with eye-catching outfits, slightly unique taste, various talents, a defence mechanism that started out as shyness, a personality that differentiates the likes and dislikes for everything and because of all this, was often treated as someone who is eccentric, I love my friend even more for all these characteristics, but for the same reasons, the friend received even more looks of hatred all this while. These lyries started out as things I wanted to say to my eccentric friend', but as I worked on this song, I realised that this is also my story. After completing the lyrics, I think it wouldn't be unnatural at all for anyone to become the main character, besides my friend or me. Because in life, we would definitely have experienced a sense of alienation for not having met expectations set by others. Including my friend, I want to tell those who were born unpolished yet unique. You're not 'byeolnan' (eccentric) but someone who is a 'byeol' (star)." - IU

(source cr: iuteamstarcandy on twt)
